result.execSummary:
The defendant Malik H. AHMAD was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Deliver Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(cm)1r.
  • Deliver Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(cm)1r.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

The Court set this status conference because of all the correspondence he has received from the defendant.  
The defendant states he does not understand the cause of action against him.  He claims he lives his life under common law under the Uniform Criminal Code.
The Court finds the defendant is subject to the jurisdiction of this court and the UCC has no jurisdiction in this matter.
The defendant is given another copy of the criminal complaint and Information which he can take back to the jail with him to read in depth.
Attorney Tarnowski has learned the identity of the confidential informant in this matter.  He has represented this person in the past which presents a conflict.  He asks that he be allowed to withdraw.
State has no objection.
Defendant has no objection.
The Court grants the motion to withdraw and tells Attorney Tarnowski to submit an order for signature.
